verbs.description: unmail (third-person singular simple present unmails, present participle unmailing, simple past and past participle unmailed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To undo the act of mailing; to recover from the postal system before delivery.
examples: Was it even possible to unmail a letter? She might have to lie, might have to say the letter contained explosives, or some kind of poison. Something extremely illegal.
